        <abstract>
            <p>Comments on BAAS meeting: "our side seems to have got on very well". Asa Gray, too, is fighting nobly.</p> 
<p>Comments on review [by Samuel Wilberforce] in the <hi rend="italic">Quarterly</hi> [<hi rend="italic">Rev.</hi> 108 (1860): 225–64].</p>  
<p>Mentions a favourable review in the <hi rend="italic">London Review</hi>.</p>  
<p>Wonders if German translation [of the <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>] by Bronn has drawn attention to the subject.</p>  
<p>The <hi rend="italic">Natural History Review</hi> to be edited by Huxley and others.</p>  
<p>Expects CL’s book [<hi rend="italic">Antiquity of man</hi> (1863)] to be a bombshell.</p> 
        </abstract>
